text: 👉👉 The movie should have continued off from Halloween H20 . Josh Harnett should have reprised his role as Laurie Strode son (John Tate) for a short role in the movie , The beginning of the movie takes place in 2011 , Michael Myers  tracks his nephew down and after an extended back and forth battle , he kills him as revenge for the events of H20 that took place 14 years earlier . And it just so happens Michael murders John purposely on Laurie Strodes birthday as a way to send her a warning . His murder goes unsolved . 7 years later now in 2018 , Laurie has taken heed and knows very well it was Michael who committed the murder of her son and ever since then has moved backed to Illinois to a neighborhood adjacent to Haddonfeild to prepare for 1 final fight to the death . No more running , No more hiding , No more fear , For the past 7 years every Halloween night , Laurie Strode has now become the hunter returning to the neighborhood of Haddonfeild in disguise with a Halloween costume of her own appearing to be just enjoying trick n treating with her now 13 year old Grandson Martin Tate (Son of John Tate) knocking on door to door but secretly has her own agenda trying to locate Michael , playfully asking the new generation of Haddonfeild residents "   "Have you seen anything out of the ordinary so far ?"  " Any scary looking people walking around with knives perhaps? "  " Any kind of screams at all tonight ? , No ? Well its Halloween... everyone is entitled to one good scare... Good Night! "  Earlier that day , Laurie Strode was casually walking and a female teenager quickly brushed past her in a panic and yelled at her other friend  Female 1 : Where were you !?!?!  Some man with a white mask was just staring at me !   *Laurie instantly stops dead in her tracks*   Female 2 : Wha.. What do you mea..  Female 1 : ( Crying Hysterically)  I felt like I was being watched , and  I turned around and saw a man past the bush watching me !!! He was just standing there... Just staring !!   Female 2 :  Im so Sor...  Female 1 : I wanna go home now , Don't ever leave me like that again !   (Female 1 and 2 walk away)   Laurie Strode slowly lifts her head up with a mischievous smile and says softly " You've come home Michael "   Later on that Halloween night , Michael Myers and Laurie Strode collided in a final confrontation .

text: I'm sure this will be awesome and it has some cool moments here in the Trailer. I didn't realize that it wasn't just ignoring the entire Film Series, but it's ignoring Halloween II (1981), and saying he just killed the 3 teenagers from Halloween (1978) and was then captured and has been held for 40 years; what the hell? Now they have actually rewritten the Original Film (because he was never captured)?   Also, as horrific it would be to have some maniac kill 3 teenagers, it wouldn't be anything after 40 years. If they made a sequel to Halloween & Halloween II, in which he killed at least 12 to 15 people, in multiple locations, that would be a huge thing (National News) and having him be captured at the end (sorta like how Halloween 4 started), that would work and make sense.   I'll watch the film and enjoy it, but it's just so strange, their both around 60 in the film, that right there is crazy; because they are showing he's a normal guy, so he's not some enigma that's survived multiple deaths.   I'll say again and again, I hate when Films just dismiss entire Franchises, that's just lazy, I want to see things end; I've seen every single Halloween film, and now, with this film, it was just a waste of time, because this film is saying those never happened (hell, Laurie's dead, she died at the beginning of Halloween: Resurrection). I want an actual ending to the Halloween Series, and the Friday the 13th Series, and Nightmare on Elm Street, Texas Chainsaw Massacre and so on; I want ending, a Final Chapter. Then Hollywood can focus on creating new characters.   Awesome Trailer, just being a Sour-Puss I guess.

text: Okay.   We all now known that Michael & Laurie are not brother and sister.   That's fine.  We get it. So, in the original Halloween extended version, why did he write "sister" on his room door, then break out and hunt Laurie down then?   Ahhhh!!!!!! The whole sister connection comes from THE FIRST MOVIE, not the second! Now, if we take away the bro/sis connection, what is his purpose of breaking out & going after her 40 years later, if there's no connection otherwise? The new storyline doesn't even fit with the original story. You can't debate & nitpick anything else, if the writers ignored Michael's motivation from the original movie.
